  In any game, movement and position are of paramount importance and so
  <span>
   GameMaker
  </span>
  has a complete selection of actions to deal with every situation. The two main ways of moving an instance is to either set the actual position (x/y) within the
    room, or to set a speed/direction vector. The actions shown here cover both methods and you can use the
  <strong>
   Common
  </strong>
  Action
  <a href="../Common/Assign_Variable.htm">
   Assign Variable
  </a>
  to directly set the x and y position yourself.
  
  
